# Q4 flag invariance
DEFERRED in this spike — see REPORT.md.
Rationale: ClasspathEntrySnapshot embeds class metadata (classId, classAbiHash,
supertypes), not compiler flags. Flag effects (-Xfriend-paths visibility,
plugin classes) modify what the compiler emits and how it resolves symbols, but
do not modify the metadata of classpath classes themselves. Risk treated as bounded;
if the implementation finds anomalies on a per-flag basis, cache key can be
extended to include a flag hash without changing the design's overall shape.
